Its effects are seen, for example, in the Constitution of the country, which includes a number of accomplishments and achievements, such as freedom of speech, freedom of religion and freedom of expression, things that were denied by the white minority regime.

I also see the Settlement at Olifantsfonteyn in KwaZuluNatal as a historic event; the Conference at Sterkfontein in Free State was a significant event. I look at South Africa as a country where change has occurred. Another important event was the visit of Nelson Mandela to the Belgium World fairs, and also the year 2000 where Nelson Mandela was awarded a Nobel Peace Prize, as well as when F.W. de Klerk was honored by the United Nations.

Turning point in the now by the author:

The turning point in my life happened during the apartheid era, when the State violated my rights as a human being; South Africa is part of me and being born during the liberation ball gave me hope for life. As a result of this situation, I faced a life-threatening challenge. I actually toiled like an elephant of Olifantsfontein – this is why I used that word as the title of my book.
